rComments: The best prof I've ever had, hands down.

Kimball was a very nice professor who was willing to help and had good knowledge of the material. She was unorganized at times but overall I thought she was a great prof. Her tests required memorization but it is a 3rd year Nutrition course, you need to know some details. Don't let other reviews throw you off, if you put in some work it'll pay off.
Not very organized. Often forgets to post slides, but are posted after lectures. Material is straightforward. Just need to read the text and follow the lectures.
First few lectures were awful and boring, but they got better as course went on. She answered emails and questions readily enough. Material not bad but exams were hard.
Disorganized lectures. The material wasn't too hard but she's a terrible lecturer.
